    leaf pmMicroTxSleepTime {
      description "Time of no radio power. Indicates total power saving time. Unit: 1 s. Applicable if the following conditions are met: - Micro Sleep Tx feature is activated. - Micro Sleep Tx-capable radios are used with only one carrier on the specific TX branch. If more than one carrier is configured on a specific TX branch, the radio only switches off the hardware related to those TX branches where no carriers are transmitting. RadioProcessing.pmTxOffTime, Rfport.pmTxOffTime or FreqBandData.pmTxOffTime can be used to observe total time transmission is switched off on hardware. Applicable to non-ESS cells and ESS FDD cells when partner LTE cell is locked..";
      type uint64;
      config false;
    }
